\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.7}{\ignorespaces BPMN-style Glucose System Cycle illustrating the circular flow of glucose dynamics in the tumor microenvironment. Blood vessels inject glucose which diffuses spatially and is consumed preferentially by tumor cells (Warburg effect), creating concentration gradients that guide immune cell chemotaxis back toward glucose-rich regions near blood vessels. This creates a continuous cycle where metabolic competition shapes spatial organization.}}{37}{figure.caption.19}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:glucose_system_cycle}{{4.7}{37}{BPMN-style Glucose System Cycle illustrating the circular flow of glucose dynamics in the tumor microenvironment. Blood vessels inject glucose which diffuses spatially and is consumed preferentially by tumor cells (Warburg effect), creating concentration gradients that guide immune cell chemotaxis back toward glucose-rich regions near blood vessels. This creates a continuous cycle where metabolic competition shapes spatial organization}{figure.caption.19}{}}
